    "description": "Aditya Birla Finance Asia Pacific Associates invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Senior Financial Analyst at our Jabalpur location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout Aditya Birla Finance Asia Pacific Associates:\nAditya Birla Finance Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBBS / MD / MS from recognized medical college\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in GST\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in Ind AS\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Learning & development budget\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Aditya Birla Finance Asia Pacific Associates!",
